response_message.content:
#!/usr/bin/env zsh

# Recursively find all PNG files and add padding, saving next to the original
find . -type f -name '*.png' -print0 | while IFS= read -r -d '' image; do
  # Preserve directory structure for the new file name
  dir="${image:h}"
  base="${image:t:r}"
  ext="${image:e}"
  new_name="${base}.padded.${ext}"
  output_path="${dir}/${new_name}"
  # assumes 70x70 original size, add padding to make it 120x120 total => 25px padding on each side
  magick "$image" -gravity center -background transparent -extent 120x120 "$output_path"
done
